      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change less than 5% between successive refinement levels using Richardson extrapolation.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the screw-rod interface region. Richardson extrapolation yielded a Grid Convergence Index of 1.8% for stiffness and 2.3% for yield force. Discretization error is within the 5% acceptance threshold."
