      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts must be documented prior to result submission.",
      "rationale": "Model setup was reviewed by a second analyst independent of the primary modeler. Boundary condition application and post-processing scripts were verified against the ASTM F1717 test fixture geometry. No use errors were identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The constitutive model must capture nonlinear plasticity of titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) and the contact formulation must represent screw-rod locking behavior consistent with published literature.",
      "rationale": "A bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V coupon data was employed. Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient 0.2 was applied at the screw-rod interface, consistent with Cordero et al. (2016). Model form is appropriate for the compression-bending regime of interest."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometric dimensions, and boundary condition parameters must be sourced from traceable measurements or certified material certificates. Uncertainty bounds must be assigned to each input.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (E = 114 ± 3 GPa), yield strength (880 ± 15 MPa), and Poisson's ratio for Ti-6Al-4V were obtained from certified material test reports. Screw geometry was digitized from CMM measurements of production hardware. Uncertainty bounds for all inputs were propagated through the Monte Carlo UQ analysis. Achieved level meets the required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least 8 experimental constructs from production-representative hardware must be tested; sample traceability to manufacturing lot must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs from two production lots were tested across two independent laboratories. All samples were traceable to manufacturing lot certificates. Sample size exceeds the minimum requirement and supports statistical comparison against the Monte Carlo output distribution."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span at least two load levels or fixture configurations representative of the clinical use envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (compression-bending at 5 mm/min displacement rate). No variation in load angle or displacement rate was explored. This limits the ability to characterize model behavior across the full COU envelope. Achieved level (2) is below the required level (3); this is the identified gap documented in the credibility assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test configuration, with documented mapping between simulation inputs and measured experimental parameters.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry, loading axis alignment, and grip compliance were measured from the physical test apparatus and mapped directly to boundary conditions in the FEA model. Equivalency of all material and geometric inputs was confirmed through the input traceability matrix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Comparison metric E/uval must be below 1.96 for all QoIs; percent difference between mean predicted and mean experimental values must be below 10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval values of 1.12, 0.87, and 1.44 were computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement respectively. Percent differences between ensemble mean predictions and experimental means were 4.1%, 2.8%, and 6.3%. All acceptance criteria are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) must be directly linked to the clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements for the pedicle screw system.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force is the primary fatigue precursor; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to catastrophic failure assessment. All three QoIs are explicitly referenced in the FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
